An Act authorizing and directing the Retirement Board of the Town of Franklin to grant
creditable service to Richard Martini.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Notwithstanding the provisions of any general or special law, rule or regulation to the
2 contrary, the Norfolk County Retirement Board is hereby authorized and directed to credit
3 Richard Martini with creditable service, for the period of July, nineteen hundred and ninety- five
4 through June, two thousand, inclusive for the purpose of determining his superannuation
5 retirement allowance pursuant to the provisions of paragraph (a) of subdivision (2) of section
6 five of chapter thirty-two of the General Laws; provided however, that before the date of any
7 retirement allowance becomes effective in the case of Richard Martini, said Richard Martini
8 shall pay into the annuity savings fund of said retirement system of said city in one sum or
9 installments, upon such terms and conditions as said board may prescribe, an annual amount
10 equal to that which would have been withheld as regular deductions from his regular
11 compensation for such previous service, plus interest.
